profile_positions.description:
•	Led the global compensation and benefits project to review, update and roll-out global total reward policies and strategies; 
•	Advised and guided Country Directors and Country HR Managers on all matters pertaining to compensation and benefits; 
•	Conduct job evaluation based on market trends to enable fair and competitive C&B- processes and procedures; 
•	Developed a global SNV job house including updating and drafting job descriptions for all the jobs in SNV globally; 
•	Led compensation and benefits benchmark analysis and implementation in all SNV countries.

•	End responsible for Strategic Human Resources Management for the Global Agriculture Sector of SNV. The Agriculture Sector comprises 60% of the workforce;  
•	Provide strategic HR advice and direction to Managing Director – Agriculture and Country Directors (CDs) across the SNV countries with needs assessment and thorough analysis of budgets; 
•	Responsible for the full breadth of the HR function in the global Agriculture sector- Recruitment & Selection, Mobility & Deployment, Talent Retention & Development, Employee Engagement and Performance Management in line with corporate HR policies; 
•	Identified talents and facilitated mentorship and coaching trajectory for personal and professional development including succession planning; 
•	Kept abreast with sector strategy, products and developments to provide sound business advice balancing the needs of sector and business; 
•	Actively use strategic insight, facts and figures and own behaviour to influence employees, and managers in a positive manner; 
•	Ensured managers were equipped for value-added conversations and to get the most out of the performance management process; supported managers under challenging discussions and play an active role in improving the feedback culture; 
•	Developed and implemented multi-annual and annual HR strategies and workforce policies; 
•	In addition to the above responsibility I also coached and mentored country HR personnel.

•	Led short and long-term internal organisational planning and strategy; 
•	Reviewed office performance, identified bottlenecks and proposed solutions to improve the operational functions and to promote efficiency and cost-effectiveness and managed changes; 
•	Conducted compensation and benefits analysis to be market aligned; 
•	Established an efficient and effective relationship with relevant external parties contributing to efficient partnerships; 
•	Developed merger strategy of SNV Bhutan and SNV Nepal and led the change management process; 
•	Identified and planned Human Resources needs in compliance with HR policies, procedures and requirements; 
•	Responsible for the full breadth of the HR function - Recruitment & Selection, Mobility & Deployment, Talent Retention & Development, Employee Engagement and Performance Management in line with corporate HR policies; 
•	Identified talents and facilitated mentorship and coaching trajectory for personal and professional development including succession planning; 
•	Assisted in the proposal writing for project bids for economic empowerment and private sector involvement; 
•	Liaised with the Regional and Head offices to maintain links and coordinate and resolve operational and policy issues; 
•	As the Safety and Security responsible, led the management of safety and security of all staff of SNV during the April and May 2015 Earthquake in Nepal: including, evacuation of international staff, logistic coordination for rescue efforts and development of emergency and safety & security plan implemented in SNV Nepal which was also adopted by other SNV countries.

•	Supported identification and planning of Human Resources needs, compliance with HR policies and procedures and requirements; 
•	Recruitment & Selection: editing job descriptions, publishing vacancies, conducting interviews, salary negotiation, contracting and onboarding; 
•	Employee engagement- built professional relationships of trust with SNV employees to enable open communication; 
•	Supported hiring managers in Human Resources and performance issues;  
•	Analysed performance appraisal to identify training and development needs and design learning plans; 
•	Created, managed and maintained HR roster/candidate pool; 
•	Assisted in proposal writing specifically on the HR aspect for project bids; 
•	Was the focal point for managers and employees on issues relating to HR administration; 
•	Liaised with the Regional and Head offices to conform to global policies and to escalate HR issues arising in the country; 
•	Assisted the country management team to develop a country HR strategy in the capacity of interim HR Officer.

•	Managed all financial and administration requirements of the company; 
•	Produced financial reports for effective business decisions: profit and loss account, balance sheet; 
•	Prepared marketing and branding strategies for business growth and improved revenue generation;  
•	Managed human resources of the company and act as a focal point for all human resources and administrative needs; 
•	Client relationship and management focusing on providing excellent customer service for long-term partnerships;  
•	Managed a team of five trainees- mentoring, coaching and training them on the job.

•	Preparation and presentation of written and numerical information; 
•	Preparation of final accounts of sole traders, partnerships, and limited companies; 
•	Investigations on organisational performance using financial analysis and investment appraisals; 
•	Preparation of monthly and quarterly management accounts and financial reports; 
•	Quarterly VAT analysis and returns, together with Corporation and Personal Tax computation; 
•	General bookkeeping; preparation of budgets, maintaining sales and purchase ledger, payroll and 
        cash accounts; 
•	Client relationship and management - focusing on providing excellent customer service.
